{"parse":{"title":"Nelson Mandela: A Biography (1999)","pageid":38939693,"revid":736053224,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">Not to be confused with <a href=\"/wiki/Mandela:_The_Authorised_Biography\" title=\"Mandela: The Authorised Biography\">Mandela: The Authorised Biography</a> or <a href=\"/wiki/Long_Walk_to_Freedom\" title=\"Long Walk to Freedom\">Long Walk to Freedom</a>.</div>\n<table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption style=\"font-style:italic;padding-bottom:0.2em;\">Nelson Mandela: A Biography <span class=\"Z3988\" title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Nelson+Mandela%3A+A+Biography&amp;rft.author=%5B%5BMartin+Meredith%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=1997&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BPublic+Affairs+Books%5D%5D&amp;rft.pages=653\"></span></caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;display:none\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Author</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Martin_Meredith\" title=\"Martin Meredith\">Martin Meredith</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Country</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/United_States\" title=\"United States\">United States</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Language</th><td>\nEnglish</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Subject</th><td>\nThe life of <a href=\"/wiki/Nelson_Mandela\" title=\"Nelson Mandela\">Nelson Mandela</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Genre</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Biography\" title=\"Biography\">Biography</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Publisher</th><td>\n<a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Public_Affairs_Books&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Public Affairs Books (page does not exist)\">Public Affairs Books</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><div style=\"padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;\">Publication date</div></th><td>\n1997</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Pages</th><td>\n653</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>Nelson Mandela: A Biography</b></i> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Biography\" title=\"Biography\">biography</a> written by <a href=\"/wiki/Martin_Meredith\" title=\"Martin Meredith\">Martin Meredith</a> on <a href=\"/wiki/Nelson_Mandela\" title=\"Nelson Mandela\">Nelson Mandela</a>. The book details Mandela's early life and major influences on him, his moving to <a href=\"/wiki/Johannesburg\" title=\"Johannesburg\">Johannesburg</a>, joining the <a href=\"/wiki/African_National_Congress\" title=\"African National Congress\">African National Congress</a>, his imprisonment on <a href=\"/wiki/Robben_Island\" title=\"Robben Island\">Robben Island</a>, and eventually, his <a href=\"/wiki/President_of_South_Africa\" title=\"President of South Africa\">Presidency</a>. Also chronicled are the rise and fall of <a href=\"/wiki/Apartheid\" title=\"Apartheid\">apartheid</a>, the scandals involving <a href=\"/wiki/Winnie_Mandela\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Winnie Mandela\">Winnie Mandela</a> (Nelson's wife), and <a href=\"/wiki/Thabo_Mbeki\" title=\"Thabo Mbeki\">Thabo Mbeki</a>'s term as President. Martina Meredith is known for authoring many books and articles on Africa and the key people within it. \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Nelson_Mandela:_A_Biography_(1999)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><i><a href=\"/wiki/Long_Walk_to_Freedom\" title=\"Long Walk to Freedom\">Long Walk to Freedom</a></i>, Mandela's autobiography</li></ul>\n<div role=\"navigation\" class=\"navbox\" aria-labelledby=\"Nelson_Mandela\" style=\"padding:3px\"><table class=\"nowraplinks hlist collapsible autocollapse navbox-inner\" style=\"border-spacing:0;background:transparent;color:inherit\"><tbody><tr><th scope=\"col\" class=\"navbox-title\" colspan=\"3\"><div class=\"plainlinks hlist navb